1
00:00:13,125 --> 00:00:19,083
[OFFICERS shouting]

2
00:00:23,916 --> 00:00:25,416
No one escapes!

3
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:28,250
You have permission to
kill anyone who resists!

4
00:00:34,416 --> 00:00:35,541
[KOSODE]
Yasusuke.

5
00:00:37,958 --> 00:00:39,750
Your torch.

6
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:40,791
Come on.

7
00:00:43,666 --> 00:00:45,541
[RAIKOU]
Wowie!

8
00:00:45,625 --> 00:00:48,416
Look at this thing. I just can't
get over how beautiful it is--

9
00:00:52,916 --> 00:00:53,916
Hold on.

10
00:00:55,708 --> 00:00:56,375
[YASUSUKE]
Don't move.

11
00:00:56,458 --> 00:00:57,416
[gasps]

12
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:03,666
Dammit.

13
00:01:07,791 --> 00:01:08,750
Go on, Kosode!

14
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:09,791
Right.

15
00:01:11,166 --> 00:01:12,125
[RAIKOU]
Huh?

16
00:01:14,625 --> 00:01:16,333
Hey. Are you all right?

17
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:24,291
[gasps]

18
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:25,875
[BOTH]
Wait, you're that guy!

19
00:03:03,750 --> 00:03:05,625
[RAIKOU]
So, what did that guy do?

20
00:03:05,708 --> 00:03:09,083
[YASUSUKE] He and some others
raided the imperial storehouse.

21
00:03:09,166 --> 00:03:11,875
Lately, we've seen an increase
in crimes of that nature.

22
00:03:11,958 --> 00:03:13,250
He stole food?

23
00:03:13,333 --> 00:03:15,875
And apparently he
cuts people, too.

24
00:03:15,958 --> 00:03:17,208
[RAIKOU]
Oh.

25
00:03:17,291 --> 00:03:19,708
It's not really necessary
to charge him for this.

26
00:03:19,791 --> 00:03:21,125
Are you certain?

27
00:03:21,208 --> 00:03:22,666
It's not too much of a wound.

28
00:03:22,750 --> 00:03:23,958
[KOSODE]
Here, let me.

29
00:03:26,375 --> 00:03:27,750
You're injured, sir.

30
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:30,375
No! It's-It's fine, really.

31
00:03:30,458 --> 00:03:31,708
I can do it.

32
00:03:31,791 --> 00:03:33,958
[YASUSUKE chuckles]

33
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,291
Well, these are probably ruined.

34
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:40,708
Yeah. They're collateral damage.

35
00:03:40,791 --> 00:03:42,000
But what can you do?

36
00:03:43,125 --> 00:03:44,750
[KOSODE]
I'll take care of that for you.

37
00:03:46,083 --> 00:03:48,416
Forgive me, sir, I never
introduced myself.

38
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:51,125
My name's Fujiwara no Yasusuke.

39
00:03:51,208 --> 00:03:54,541
And this is my
discharge, Kosode.

40
00:03:54,625 --> 00:03:55,875
[RAIKOU]
"Discharge"?

41
00:03:55,958 --> 00:03:59,375
Yes. I was granted a
documentation of innocence,

42
00:03:59,458 --> 00:04:01,125
and released from prison
under the condition

43
00:04:01,208 --> 00:04:03,041
that I work for Yasusuke.

44
00:04:03,125 --> 00:04:05,958
But I was locked up for
the same crime as that man.

45
00:04:06,041 --> 00:04:07,166
[RAIKOU]
I see.

46
00:04:07,250 --> 00:04:09,375
You must've had a pretty
hard life then, huh?

47
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:10,541
[KOSODE]
Uh?

48
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:14,166
You are... a very strange man.

49
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,125
Ha, the name is Raikou.

50
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:23,875
That man, the one
we ran into earlier?

51
00:04:23,958 --> 00:04:26,708
You know, it's funny, but he
kinda reminded me of you.

52
00:04:26,791 --> 00:04:28,708
What? Really?

53
00:04:30,166 --> 00:04:31,875
Well, I guess we ought
to be getting back

54
00:04:31,958 --> 00:04:34,000
to your brother soon,
wouldn't you say?

55
00:04:34,083 --> 00:04:37,250
Oh, no, the banquet will
go on all night, I'm sure.

56
00:04:37,333 --> 00:04:38,750
It doesn't matter.

57
00:04:38,833 --> 00:04:40,500
It does, Yasuske.

58
00:04:42,208 --> 00:04:46,291
Kosode... This is... for you.

59
00:04:49,958 --> 00:04:54,041
I'm still a discharge,
someone who committed a crime.

60
00:04:54,125 --> 00:04:55,375
Yeah.

61
00:04:55,458 --> 00:04:57,750
Well, I found this stone
near the Kamogawa river

62
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:59,250
and polished it for you.

63
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:01,625
I mean, I know that noblewomen
never let their hair down

64
00:05:01,708 --> 00:05:02,791
or use pins like this,

65
00:05:02,875 --> 00:05:05,625
but... it's just...

66
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:07,791
...I like the way that
you wear your hair.

67
00:05:12,875 --> 00:05:13,958
Damn.

68
00:05:15,375 --> 00:05:17,625
If you don't like it,
then you can throw it away.

69
00:05:17,708 --> 00:05:19,958
Please, I...

70
00:05:20,041 --> 00:05:23,500
Well, I don't feel like
it, but we should go.

71
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:34,166
[SEIMEI]
Oh, that Raikou.

72
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:36,000
He should've secured
our food supply

73
00:05:36,083 --> 00:05:38,166
before securing the peace.

74
00:05:45,875 --> 00:05:47,875
Oh, pardon me.

75
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:50,583
Whoa, that's rare!

76
00:05:50,666 --> 00:05:52,541
[KOSODE]
Once you begin stealing,

77
00:05:52,625 --> 00:05:56,125
lady, you can never turn back.

78
00:05:56,208 --> 00:05:58,125
Well, aren't you
a rude little girl.

79
00:05:58,208 --> 00:06:01,208
I just saw some rare pottery
that I wanted, so I took it.

80
00:06:01,291 --> 00:06:03,708
That's the very
definition of a thief.

81
00:06:03,791 --> 00:06:05,791
Huh. Guess so.

82
00:06:05,875 --> 00:06:07,333
No, no, no, no, no!

83
00:06:07,416 --> 00:06:09,250
Are you by any chance
hungry, ma'am?

84
00:06:09,333 --> 00:06:11,375
No, I'm not!

85
00:06:11,458 --> 00:06:13,833
[stomach growling]

86
00:06:13,916 --> 00:06:16,583
[groaning]

87
00:06:16,666 --> 00:06:20,333
[SEIMEI]
I swear, I'm not!

88
00:06:21,416 --> 00:06:23,750
[SEIMEI]
Mm, that's delicious!

89
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:27,541
Seriously, this potato ball
is absolutely incredible!

90
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:30,166
I mean, the kneaded potato skin
and the crushed bean paste

91
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:32,583
go together in perfect harmony!

92
00:06:32,666 --> 00:06:34,083
That's all there is.

93
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:36,791
Originally, that wasn't
even my potato.

94
00:06:36,875 --> 00:06:39,500
I want more. I have
to have more! Now!

95
00:06:39,583 --> 00:06:41,625
But there isn't any.

96
00:06:41,708 --> 00:06:43,250
Stingy.

97
00:06:43,333 --> 00:06:46,333
[KOSODE] Well, now, guess I
could make something else.

98
00:06:51,916 --> 00:06:52,750
Uh?

99
00:06:52,833 --> 00:06:54,000
Hey! What the--?

100
00:06:54,083 --> 00:06:55,333
[SEIMEI] You know,
your clothes may be drab,

101
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:58,166
but that hair ornament
really is quite beautiful.

102
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:02,000
Beautiful, and yet,
somehow incomplete.

103
00:07:02,083 --> 00:07:04,125
I want it! Give it to me!

104
00:07:04,208 --> 00:07:05,750
I'll trade you all
kinds of things for it!

105
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:07,250
More valuable things!

106
00:07:07,333 --> 00:07:09,125
Come on, there has to be
something that you want!

107
00:07:09,208 --> 00:07:10,291
You mean to trade?

108
00:07:10,375 --> 00:07:11,958
So you really aren't
a thief, after all?

109
00:07:12,041 --> 00:07:14,291
I told you, you had
the wrong idea about me!

110
00:07:14,375 --> 00:07:15,541
I'm begging you!

111
00:07:16,625 --> 00:07:17,958
Pretty please?

112
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,166
If you're not lying, and
you want it that badly.

113
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:27,541
Well, then fine.
You can have it.

114
00:07:28,708 --> 00:07:32,458
[ARISTOCRATS chuckling]

115
00:07:32,541 --> 00:07:36,083
[MASAMUNE] Oh, my.
A maple tree from Michinaga.

116
00:07:36,166 --> 00:07:38,625
It is truly a marvelous thing.

117
00:07:38,708 --> 00:07:42,208
Yes, and such a
beautiful color.

118
00:07:42,291 --> 00:07:44,125
[MASAMUNE] He carried it
down from Ogura Mountain

119
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:46,083
in just one day.

120
00:07:46,166 --> 00:07:49,166
What a wonderful display of
Michinaga's immense strength,

121
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:53,208
not to mention, a powerful
symbol of his trust in Yasumasa.

122
00:07:53,291 --> 00:07:56,500
Is it not, eh, Yorinobu?

123
00:07:56,583 --> 00:07:58,500
It is.

124
00:07:58,583 --> 00:08:00,708
Oh, I concur wholeheartedly.

125
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:04,083
It really is splendid.
Quite splendid.

126
00:08:04,166 --> 00:08:06,166
[ARISTOCRATS chuckling]

127
00:08:07,916 --> 00:08:09,500
[YASUMASA]
Yasuske, a few days ago,

128
00:08:09,583 --> 00:08:12,625
you challenged Michinaga
in front of Kintou.

129
00:08:12,708 --> 00:08:14,833
[YASUSKE] In the face of
constantly rising crime,

130
00:08:14,916 --> 00:08:16,416
he sits back and does nothing.

131
00:08:16,500 --> 00:08:19,708
And the conflict at his home
ended without any explanation.

132
00:08:19,791 --> 00:08:22,375
Well, that's because he
owes you no explanation.

133
00:08:22,458 --> 00:08:23,625
Just leave it alone.

134
00:08:23,708 --> 00:08:24,708
Yes, but, brother--

135
00:08:24,791 --> 00:08:26,291
I'm not finished.

136
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:29,750
I also hear you've been getting
awfully close to your discharge.

137
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:31,041
[gasps]

138
00:08:31,125 --> 00:08:34,041
I do hope that's just a rumor.

139
00:08:34,125 --> 00:08:36,583
It doesn't matter to me
what she is or used to be.

140
00:08:36,666 --> 00:08:38,500
I do not care.

141
00:08:38,583 --> 00:08:41,375
[YASUMASA] I am not
interested in how you feel.

142
00:08:41,458 --> 00:08:45,500
The blood of the Fujiwada family
courses through your veins.

143
00:08:45,583 --> 00:08:47,916
I trust you understand
what that means.

144
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,958
[grunts]

145
00:08:50,041 --> 00:08:51,166
[YASUMASA]
I won't tolerate any more

146
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:55,208
of this gallivanting
about with her.

147
00:08:55,291 --> 00:08:58,958
Now, will you obey and bring
honor to our family name,

148
00:08:59,041 --> 00:09:01,333
or will you side
with that criminal?

149
00:09:10,708 --> 00:09:13,041
[RAIKOU]
Yummy!

150
00:09:13,125 --> 00:09:15,625
The ground up potato skin
mixed with the red bean paste

151
00:09:15,708 --> 00:09:17,291
are the perfect combination.

152
00:09:17,375 --> 00:09:19,458
Kosode used the crushed
potatoes from last night

153
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:20,583
to make them.

154
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:22,375
Wow, she made this
outta those things?

155
00:09:22,458 --> 00:09:25,458
Really? That takes some skill.

156
00:09:25,541 --> 00:09:26,833
So where's the chef now?

157
00:09:26,916 --> 00:09:28,458
[YASUSUKE] Oh, she had
a pressing engagement

158
00:09:28,541 --> 00:09:30,375
to attend to today.

159
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:31,750
I see.

160
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:33,958
Too bad, I would have liked
to thank her personally.

161
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:35,583
[YASUSUKE]
Don't worry.

162
00:09:35,666 --> 00:09:39,625
In fact, I actually came here
to talk to you about something.

163
00:09:39,708 --> 00:09:40,666
[RAIKOU]
Hm?

164
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,500
Hey, I'm gonna go
put some tea on, okay.

165
00:09:47,583 --> 00:09:48,791
All right, the thing is,

166
00:09:48,875 --> 00:09:51,166
I'm thinking about asking
Kosode to marry me.

167
00:09:51,250 --> 00:09:52,333
[RAIKOU gasps]

168
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:54,500
Seriously? You can't.
You're the police.

169
00:09:54,583 --> 00:09:58,458
And Kosode is a... a...

170
00:09:58,541 --> 00:10:01,500
So then, you're the
same as all the rest.

171
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:03,875
Look, it's not that I think
Kosode's a bad person,

172
00:10:03,958 --> 00:10:06,416
it's only, you know...

173
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:07,708
[YASUSUKE]
Well,

174
00:10:07,791 --> 00:10:09,916
what if we were both
criminals, how about then?

175
00:10:12,208 --> 00:10:14,750
Don't even think about
doing something so stupid.

176
00:10:14,833 --> 00:10:16,666
Yasuske, you've
devoted your life

177
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:18,541
to leading people
down the right path.

178
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:20,333
Don't stray from
it now yourself.

179
00:10:20,416 --> 00:10:23,458
Instead, you should work to get
everyone else to accept Kosode.

180
00:10:24,583 --> 00:10:27,000
Don't stray from
the right path, huh?

181
00:10:27,083 --> 00:10:29,416
You are straight as an arrow.

182
00:10:29,500 --> 00:10:33,083
But you see, Raikou,
the real problem is,

183
00:10:33,166 --> 00:10:35,916
looking at this capital now,
I'm beginning to believe

184
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,583
that all the so-called
criminals are, in fact,

185
00:10:38,666 --> 00:10:40,000
the righteous ones.

186
00:10:51,583 --> 00:10:53,125
Wow.

187
00:10:53,208 --> 00:10:54,166
Nice, right?

188
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:56,208
I can't believe that you did it.

189
00:10:56,291 --> 00:10:58,166
You really were able
to pull this off.

190
00:10:58,250 --> 00:11:01,458
Oh, all it takes is charming
an aristocrat here and there.

191
00:11:01,541 --> 00:11:03,916
Who are you?
Where'd you come from?

192
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:07,041
These people, they live in
constant fear of evil spirits,

193
00:11:07,125 --> 00:11:09,750
and throw obscenely
decadent parties.

194
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:13,000
What a collection of
cowards and scumbags.

195
00:11:13,083 --> 00:11:14,375
That may be, but...

196
00:11:14,458 --> 00:11:16,666
...I still long to achieve
a higher status...

197
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:18,750
...to wear the finest kimonos.

198
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,708
Ah, so that's how it is.

199
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:21,750
[gasps]

200
00:11:25,541 --> 00:11:26,750
What do I do?

201
00:11:26,833 --> 00:11:28,208
[SEIMEI]
Hold your head high.

202
00:11:40,083 --> 00:11:41,333
[KOSODE]
Please stop.

203
00:11:42,666 --> 00:11:45,083
I... I've had enough now.

204
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:50,291
[SEIMEI] That little ride
really was enough for you?

205
00:11:50,375 --> 00:11:51,500
[KOSODE]
Yes.

206
00:11:51,583 --> 00:11:53,166
I guess that I'm just
not really cut out

207
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:54,833
for the high life after all.

208
00:11:55,916 --> 00:11:58,791
So tell me, are you in
love with an aristocrat?

209
00:12:01,166 --> 00:12:03,375
The man who gave me
this hair stick,

210
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:06,625
well, he was the police official
who caught me stealing.

211
00:12:08,208 --> 00:12:10,291
You wanna forget him.

212
00:12:10,375 --> 00:12:14,416
No. You're letting it go 'cause
you want him to forget you.

213
00:12:16,083 --> 00:12:18,291
[SEIMEI] Now don't go and
ask for it back later.

214
00:12:20,958 --> 00:12:22,583
[KOSODE]
Don't worry, I won't.

215
00:12:24,125 --> 00:12:26,250
He already gave me
something far more valuable

216
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:27,791
than a hair trinket.

217
00:12:49,041 --> 00:12:51,458
Today... was dangerous.

218
00:12:54,375 --> 00:12:55,541
[YASUSUKE]
That's enough.

219
00:12:56,958 --> 00:12:58,375
[KOSODE]
We can't do this.

220
00:13:01,875 --> 00:13:04,333
[YASUSUKE]
Kosode. With you, I--

221
00:13:04,416 --> 00:13:06,750
[KOSODE]
Yasusuke.

222
00:13:06,833 --> 00:13:09,083
I want you to let me go.

223
00:13:09,166 --> 00:13:10,583
[YASUSUKE gasps]

224
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:12,500
Wait, what do you mean?

225
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:14,500
[KOSODE]
Exactly what I said.

226
00:13:14,583 --> 00:13:18,041
I can't be with you anymore,
Yasusuke. I just can't.

227
00:13:18,125 --> 00:13:19,541
[YASUSUKE]
Tell me why.

228
00:13:19,625 --> 00:13:21,583
[KOSODE] Because you carry
the Fujiwara name.

229
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:22,750
[YASUSUKE]
I told you!

230
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:24,750
I don't care about
my family or my name.

231
00:13:24,833 --> 00:13:26,541
[KOSODE]
You don't get it, do you?

232
00:13:26,625 --> 00:13:28,125
The only reason I
became a criminal

233
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:30,666
was because I had no
other choice in life!

234
00:13:30,750 --> 00:13:32,166
And now you're just
gonna walk away

235
00:13:32,250 --> 00:13:34,250
from the good life
you were born into?

236
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:35,750
Why would I want
to be with a fool

237
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:39,166
who doesn't appreciate what
he has, and is so reckless?

238
00:13:40,416 --> 00:13:41,500
Hold on!

239
00:13:41,583 --> 00:13:43,666
Where's the hair
stick I gave you?

240
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:45,916
[KOSODE]
I don't have any need for it.

241
00:13:49,291 --> 00:13:53,250
Every single day, the people
around us die of hunger.

242
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:55,291
Don't act like you don't see it!

243
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:58,166
Maybe. But crime
must be punished.

244
00:13:58,250 --> 00:14:02,250
[KOSODE] Your idea of justice...
I don't have any need for it!

245
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:06,916
[YASUSUKE]
Kosode.

246
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:11,250
[SEIMEI]
Hey,

247
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:13,458
Kintoki said we couldn't have
dinner until you got back.

248
00:14:13,541 --> 00:14:14,791
Yeah.

249
00:14:14,875 --> 00:14:16,291
[SEIMEI] Your face looks
like a soggy rice cracker

250
